  ‚û• darken(), lighten() functions
‚Ä¢ cli basic commands such as: 
  ‚û• dir(list files & folders in directory)
  ‚û• mkdir(create folder)
  ‚û• echo > file1.txt echo > file2.txt (creates multiple files)
  ‚û• rmdir /s /q (delete folder) 
    ‚û• (s = all files & subdirectories)
    ‚û• (q = quiet mode, no confirmation prompts)
  ‚û• del(delete files)

Basic Responsive Design Principles
1. Fluid Grids & Layouts
  ‚û• To allow content to easily adapt to the current viewport width used to browse
the website. Uses % rather than px for all layout-related lengths.
2. Flexible / Responsive images
  ‚û• Images behave differently than text content, and so we need to ensure that
they also adapt nicely to the current viewport.
3. Media Queries
  ‚û• To change styles on certain viewport widths (breakpoints), allowing us to
create different version of our website for different widths.

Layout Types
1. Float
2. Flexbox
3. CSS Grid

